      • toByteArray

        public byte[] toByteArray()
        Description copied from class: IPAddress
        Returns a byte array representation of this IP address. Its size is equal to IPAddress.bits() divided by Byte.SIZE. Furthermore, the result is in network byte order; the highest order byte is in the first element.
        Specified by:

        Returns:

      • toIPv6

        public IPv6Address toIPv6()
        Returns an IPv6 representation of this IPv4 address. This IPv6 address is equivalent to ::ffff:d.d.d.d, where d.d.d.d represents this IPv4 address.
        Returns:
        An IPv6 representation of this IPv4 address.

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Object o)
        Description copied from class: IPAddress
        Tests whether or not another object is equal to this IP address. An object is equal if it is a IP address with an equal return value of IPAddress.toByteArray().

        Implementations do not necessary need to use IPAddress.toByteArray(), as long as equal IP addresses also have equal byte array representations.

        Specified by:
        equals in class IPAddress<IPv4Address>

      • isMulticastAddress

        public boolean isMulticastAddress()
        Returns whether or not this IP address is an IP multicast address. An IP multicast address is a Class D address, which means the first four bits of the address are 1110. In other words, this method returns whether or not the IP address is in range 224.0.0.0 through 239.255.255.255.
        Specified by:
        isMulticastAddress in class IPAddress<IPv4Address>
        Returns:
        true if this IP address is an IP multicast address, or false otherwise.
        See Also:
        Inet4Address.isMulticastAddress()

      • valueOf

        public static IPv4Address valueOf(int octet1,
                                  int octet2,
                                  int octet3,
                                  int octet4)
        Returns an IPv4 address from four octets. For example, valueOf(192, 168, 0, 1) will return an IPv4 address that represents 192.168.0.1.
        Parameters:
        octet1 - The first octet.
        octet2 - The second octet.
        octet3 - The third octet.
        octet4 - The fourth octet.
        Returns:
        An IPv4 address that represents the given octets.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If any of the octets is not between 0 and 255, inclusive.

      • getNetmask

        public static IPv4Address getNetmask(int prefixLength)
        Returns an IPv4 address for a specific net mask.
        Parameters:
        prefixLength - The prefix length of the subnet for the net mask. For instance, 0 represents a net mask for /0 which is 0.0.0.0, 8 represents a net mask for a class A network /8 which is 255.0.0.0, 16 represents a net mask for a class B network /16 which is 255.255.0.0, 24 represents a net mask for a class C network /24 which is 255.255.255.0, etc.
        Returns:
        An IPv4 address representing a net mask with the given number of bits.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the number of bits is not between 0 and 32, inclusive.

      • isValidNetmask

        public boolean isValidNetmask()
        Returns whether or not this IPv4 address would be a valid netmask. An IPv4 address would be a valid netmask if only its left-most bits are 1s.
        Returns:
        true if this IPv4 address would be a valid netmask, or false otherwise.
